\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Training dynamics and IBR diagnostics averaged over independent seeds. \textbf  {(a)} Fixed-mixture and alternating stress approaches readily acquire nominal proficiency without catastrophic gameplay degradation. \textbf  {(b)} Direct targeted adversarial exposure effectively limits extreme worst-case trajectory vulnerabilities, explicitly lowering tail severity ($\mathrm  {CVaR}_{0.10}$ and $p95$). \textbf  {(c)} In Stage 2, tracked IBR metrics show that sufficient optimization bandwidth can yield positive \textsf  {defender\_adversarial} shifts and subsequent \textsf  {attacker\_adaptation}; these curves should be read as theorem-motivated diagnostics rather than as exact row-wise certificates.}}{22}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:all_diagnostics}{{1}{22}{Training dynamics and IBR diagnostics averaged over independent seeds. \textbf {(a)} Fixed-mixture and alternating stress approaches readily acquire nominal proficiency without catastrophic gameplay degradation. \textbf {(b)} Direct targeted adversarial exposure effectively limits extreme worst-case trajectory vulnerabilities, explicitly lowering tail severity ($\cvar _{0.10}$ and $p95$). \textbf {(c)} In Stage 2, tracked IBR metrics show that sufficient optimization bandwidth can yield positive \textsf {defender\_adversarial} shifts and subsequent \textsf {attacker\_adaptation}; these curves should be read as theorem-motivated diagnostics rather than as exact row-wise certificates}{figure.caption.7}{}}
